pcsc-tools
------------------------------------------
The pcsc-tools package contains some useful tools for a PC/SC user: pcsc_scan
regularly scans connected PC/SC smart card readers and prints detected events,
ATR_analysis analyzes smart card ATRs (Anwser To Reset), scriptor sends
commands to a smart card, and gscriptor does that from a GTK user interface.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libpcsclite1-1.8.26-1bl1
  perl_base-5.26.3-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://ludovic.rousseau.free.fr/softwares/pcsc-tools/

Canonical download:
  http://ludovic.rousseau.free.fr/softwares/pcsc-tools/pcsc-tools-1.5.5.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack pcsc-tools-1.5.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./pcsc-tools-1.5.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pcsc-tools-1.5.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/pcsc-tools-1.5.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pcsc-tools)
  /usr/bin/ATR_analysis
  /usr/bin/gscriptor
  /usr/bin/pcsc_scan.exe
  /usr/bin/scriptor
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pcsc-tools.README
  /usr/share/doc/pcsc-tools/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/pcsc-tools/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/ATR_analysis.1p.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/gscriptor.1p.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/pcsc_scan.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/scriptor.1p.gz
  /usr/share/pcsc/smartcard_list.txt

